=== test.179: tiny TCM verify after safe NVRAM marker readback — stage=0 ===
Date: Mon Apr 20 18:34:04 BST 2026

Stage 0: skip_arm=1 — download_fw_nvram: enter_download_state (read-only) + BAR2 ioread32 probe + 442KB iowrite32 fw; sleeps 100 ms, reads host resetintr from fw->data, writes NVRAM to BAR2, reads the ramsize-4 NVRAM marker, reads TCM[0x0..0x1c], releases fw/NVRAM, returns -ENODEV.
(test.179: test.178 proved the NVRAM marker readback survives. This run adds only a tiny 8-word TCM verify dump before release/return. Still no post-write ARM probe, device resetintr use, exit-download-state, broad TCM dump, or ARM release.)

=== Pre-test BAR0 MMIO guard ===
BAR0 MMIO UR/I/O error (6ms) — device alive; SBR in probe should fix. Proceeding.

